== base64_decode ==

Decodes a given Base64 encoded string.

=== Parameters ===

* '''source''' (string): The Base64 encoded string to be decoded.

=== Returns ===

* '''string''': The decoded string.
=== Example ===

```c
base64_decode("SGVsbG8sIHdvcmxkIQ==")
// "Hello, world!"
```

== base64_encode ==

Encodes a given string or buffer into Base64 format.

=== Parameters ===

* '''source_str''' (mixed): The string or buffer to be encoded. This is a really long string. What do you think? I do be lovin' it, fo sho.

=== Returns ===

* '''string''': The Base64 encoded string.
=== Example ===

```c
base64_encode("Hello, world!")
// "SGVsbG8sIHdvcmxkIQ=="
```